From: Bill Kuzeja <William.Kuzeja@stratus.com>
Date: Mon, 5 Nov 2018 11:23:50 -0500
Subject: scsi: qla2xxx: Timeouts occur on surprise removal of QLogic adapter
Git-commit: f2ffd4e5bc7b629b312be48fbe3c3a2afbd67e4a
Patch-mainline: v4.20-rc4
References: bsc#1124985

When doing a surprise removal of an adapter, some in flight I/Os can get
stuck and take a while to complete (they actually time out and are
retried). We are not handling an early error exit from qla2xxx_eh_abort
properly.

Fixes: 45235022da99 ("scsi: qla2xxx: Fix driver unload by shutting down chip")
Signed-off-by: Bill Kuzeja <william.kuzeja@stratus.com>
Reviewed-by: Laurence Oberman <loberman@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Himanshu Madhani <himanshu.madhani@cavium.com>
Signed-off-by: Martin K. Petersen <martin.petersen@oracle.com>
Acked-by: Johannes Thumshirn <jthumshirn@suse.de>
---
 drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_os.c |    8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_os.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_os.c
@@ -1805,6 +1805,12 @@ __qla2x00_abort_all_cmds(struct qla_qpai
 						    GET_CMD_SP(sp));
 						spin_lock_irqsave
 							(qp->qp_lock_ptr, flags);
+						/*
+						 * Get rid of extra reference caused
+						 * by early exit from qla2xxx_eh_abort
+						 */
+						if (status == FAST_IO_FAIL)
+							atomic_dec(&sp->ref_count);
 					}
 				}
 				sp->done(sp, res);

